  "prompt": "What is the best budget camera phone?",
  "response": "As of 2023, there are several budget-friendly smartphones that offer excellent camera performance for their price. Here are some of the best options:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Google Pixel 6a**\n- **Why it's great:** Known for its outstanding camera quality, thanks to Google\u2019s advanced computational photography.\n- **Key features:**\n  - 12.2 MP main camera\n  - Night Sight, Portrait Mode, and HDR+\n  - Affordable price for Pixel-quality photos\n  - Clean Android experience with long-term software support\n- **Approx. price:** $349\n\n---\n\n### **2. Samsung Galaxy A54 5G**\n- **Why it's great:** A versatile mid-range phone with a solid camera system and polished design.\n- **Key features:**\n  - 50 MP main camera\n  - 12 MP ultra-wide and 5 MP macro cameras\n  - Good low-light performance\n  - Reliable software updates\n- **Approx. price:** $449\n\n---\n\n### **3. iPhone SE (2022)**\n- **Why it's great:** Compact design with Apple\u2019s powerful A15 Bionic chip and excellent camera software.\n- **Key features:**\n  - 12 MP single camera with Smart HDR\n  - Portrait mode and cinematic video\n  - iOS ecosystem and long-term updates\n- **Approx. price:** $429\n\n---\n\n### **4. Xiaomi Redmi Note 12 Pro**\n- **Why it's great:** Excellent value for money with a high-quality camera setup.\n- **Key features:**\n  - 50 MP main camera with OIS\n  - 8 MP ultra-wide and 2 MP macro cameras\n  - AMOLED display\n  - Large battery and fast charging\n- **Approx. price:** $299\n\n---\n\n### **5. OnePlus Nord N30 5G**\n- **Why it's great:** Affordable with a fast 108 MP main camera.\n- **Key features:**\n  - 108 MP main sensor\n  - Macro and depth cameras\n  - Smooth 120Hz display\n  - Good performance for the price\n- **Approx. price:** $299\n\n---\n\n### **6. Moto G Power 5G (2023)**\n- **Why it's great:** Budget-friendly with decent cameras and a massive battery.\n- **Key features:**\n  - 50 MP main camera\n  - 2 MP macro and depth sensors\n  - 5000mAh battery\n  - Clean Android experience\n- **Approx. price:** $249\n\n---\n\n### **Conclusion:**\n- **Best overall:** **Google Pixel 6a** (for camera quality and software experience).\n- **Best Samsung option:** **Galaxy A54 5G** (for versatility and build quality).\n- **Best iPhone:** **iPhone SE (2022)** (for iOS fans and compact design).\n- **Best budget option:** **Xiaomi Redmi Note 12 Pro** (for features under $300).\n\nYour choice will depend on your specific needs, such as ecosystem preference, camera features, or budget.",
